  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "HCZTcxYqNtJ0IbIgwzbWsJWv8Ow=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# batch multiple actions in a single addActions call to minimize round trips\n\nThe `addActions` MCP tool accepts an array of actions. Instead of making separate calls for each operation, batch them:\n\n```typescript\n// \u2705 One call with multiple actions\naddActions({\n  documentId: \"...\",\n  actions: [\n    { type: \"SET_MODEL_NAME\", scope: \"global\", input: { name: \"Invoice\" } },\n    { type: \"SET_MODEL_DESCRIPTION\", scope: \"global\", input: { description: \"...\" } },\n    { type: \"ADD_MODULE\", scope: \"global\", input: { id: \"...\", name: \"header\" } },\n  ]\n});\n\n// \u274c Three separate calls \u2014 slower and more failure-prone\n```\n\nBatching reduces network overhead and ensures related changes are applied atomically. If one action in a batch fails, the error is visible without having lost context from intermediate calls.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[mcp workflows]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
